#                                                                              #
#                                  cub3D                                       #
#                       The 42 Raycasting Project                              #
#                                                                              #
################################################################################

[ PROJECT OVERVIEW ]
cub3D is a C-based 3D engine that utilizes the Raycasting technique to render
a 2D map into a first-person 3D perspective. Inspired by Wolfenstein 3D, this
project emphasizes low-level graphics programming, mathematical optimization,
and strict adherence to the 42 Norm standards.

[ FEATURES ]
- Smooth First-Person Movement: WASD for movement and Arrows for rotation.
- Wall Texturing: Unique XPM textures for North, South, East, and West faces.
- Sprite Engine: Interactive 2D entities (sprites) with distance sorting.
- Depth Handling: 1D Z-Buffer to prevent sprites from clipping through walls.
- Dynamic UI:
    * Custom 5x7 Bitmap Font for text rendering.
    * Score panel and animated Progress Bar.
- Sprite Animation: Sine-wave "jump" effects for sprites.
- Map Validation: Flood-fill algorithm to ensure the map is closed.



[ TECHNICAL SPECIFICATIONS ]
- Language: C
- Graphics Library: MiniLibX
- Coding Standard: 42 Norm (Max 25 lines per function, 4 arguments max).
- Core Algorithms:
    * DDA (Digital Differential Analyzer) for wall collisions.
    * Vector-based camera plane transformation for Sprites.
    * Painter's Algorithm (Sorting) for correct transparency rendering.

[ COMPILATION & EXECUTION ]
To compile the project, run:
    make

To launch the engine with a specific map:
    ./cub3D maps/bonus.cub

[ CONTROLS ]
- W, A, S, D : Move forward, backward, left, and right.
- LEFT/RIGHT : Rotate the camera view.
- Mouse      : Rotate the camera view.
- O			 : Open door.
- ESC        : Close the game safely.


[ MAP RULES ]
Map files (.cub) must include:
- Texture paths: NO, SO, WE, EA.
- Colors: F (Floor) and C (Ceiling) in R,G,B format.
- Grid: 
    1 = Wall
    0 = Empty Space
    2 = Sprite (Item)
	D = Door
    N/S/E/W = Player Starting Position & Direction

[ PROJECT STRUCTURE ]
/src        - Core logic (raycasting, movement, parsing)
#/src_bonus  - Enhanced features (sprites, UI, animations) //
/includes   - Header files and structure definitions
/textures   - XPM assets

[ DEVELOPER NOTE ]
This engine was built from scratch without any high-level 3D libraries. 
Every pixel rendered is the result of direct mathematical calculation 
projected onto a 2D buffer.

